am, which will review and decide on the PR/issue."}, {"id": 630652267, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWw2MzA2NTIyNjc=", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/labels/C-feature-request", "name": "C-feature-request", "color": "f5f1fd", "default": false, "description": "Category: A feature request, i.e: not implemented / a PR."}], "state": "open", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 4, "created_at": "2014-12-28T08:06:51Z", "updated_at": "2020-04-30T18:43:15Z", "closed_at": null, "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "```\nmacro_rules! impl_somethingable {\n    ($Base: ty, $Block:ty) => {\n        impl<'a, T> Somethingable for $Block where T: $Base {\n        }\n    }\n}\n\nimpl_somethingable!(ATrait, A);\n```\n\n```\n<anon>:15:52: 15:60 error: each predicate in a `where` clause must have at least one bound in it\n<anon>:15         impl<'a, T> Somethingable for $Block where T: $Base {\n                                                             ^~~~~~~~\n<anon>:15:56: 15:60 error: expected one of `,` or `{`, found `ATrait`\n<anon>:15         impl<'a, T> Somethingable for $Block where T: $Base {\n                                                                 ^~~~\n```\n\nThe solution is to use `$ident` instead of `$ty`, but this is non-obvious to the user, especially since it's perfectly ok to have `ATrait` in that location.\n\nPlaypen: http://is.gd/AMUJDw\n\ncc @huonw \n", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/20272/reactions", "total_count": 1, "+1": 1, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/20272/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null}